# Workspace trees are written by the pipeline, never committed. Track the empty
# skeleton (via the .gitkeep files) but ignore everything dropped into it:
# recordings, motion-corrected movies, trained weights, per-recording results,
# job logs. This keeps `git status` clean even with GBs of data sitting in place,
# and is what `git archive` honours when packing a release tarball.
#
# The `!<tree>/**/` lines re-include directories at every depth so the .gitkeep
# placeholders below them are reachable (git cannot re-include a file whose
# parent directory is excluded). Content files still match the `<tree>/**`
# ignore and stay out.
data/**
models/**
results/**
logs/**
!data/**/
!models/**/
!results/**/
!logs/**/
!**/.gitkeep

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.cache/
